						               													<description>ANTIFA is a cooperative management simulation game where you play a local antifascist group.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each month, the group will face several far-right actions. Players collectively allow activities to the far right actions they want to counteract, then each of them will take their turns assigning one of their militant tokens to a slot to increase the activity's efficiency until the group runs out of time or money. Once a token is placed it cannot be removed or moved. Discussion is highly recommended.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After the organisation phase, mishap cards are drawn for each action taken and may change the result. Weather also have a say in the matter by the roll of a die.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If the group managed to counter a far-right exaction (indicated by the efficiency level reached for that activity), their morale will increase, otherwise it will decrease.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For some activities there is also a risk of getting arrested and even put to trial.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The end of the game is quite open, the players may decide of their objectives (a certain level of morale after a specific number of months) or they can use one of the included scenarios (objectives to reach within a time limit).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
